Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Dip chicken in milk; coat with crumbs. Cook chicken in hot oil in large skillet over medium heat 10 minutes or until no longer pink, turning once. Remove chicken; keep warm. Stir undrained tomatoes, tomato paste and 1/2 cup water into skillet. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 3 minutes or until heated through. Serve sauce over chicken and fettuccine. Sprinkle with cheese. Garnish with fresh basil, if desired.